[SN]TITLE[SN]
Woman seriously hurt after being hit by van in Edinburgh

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A 19-year-old woman has been seriously injured after being hit by a van in Edinburgh.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The accident, which involved a white Vauxhall Astra van, happened on the A701 Howden Hall Road in Kaimes at about 07:50.
The woman was taken to Edinburgh Royal Infirmary.
The road was closed between Alnwickhill Road and Burdiehouse Road but has since reopened. Police appealed for anyone with information to contact them.
